                        <seg type="docType">Grant.</seg>
                        <orgName key="org_112039">Bordesley, Cistercian abbey</orgName>. <origDate notBefore="1241" notAfter="1245">[c.1241-1245] (1245). </origDate>. Grant from Geoffrey de Beniggewrth,, son of William de Beniggewrth, to the abbot and convent of Bordeslege in perpetual fee farm the whole of his lands with rents and all appurtenances of Houteselva and Tysho, and of Pilardinton and Whatcote in the county of "Warewic, paying annually to him and his heirs one mark of silver in the church of All Saints, Norhamton, and to the chief lord of Tysho 4s., and to the prior of Pilardinton in one year 10s., and in another year 11s. 4d. Witness: Philip de Assellis, then sheriff of Warewic.</p>
